  <h1>
   gpu_set_state
  </h1>
  This function will set the current GPU state using the passed-in
  <a href="../../Data_Structures/DS_Maps/DS_Maps.htm">
   DS Map
  </a>
  . The supplied map can be created using the function
  <span>
   <a href="gpu_get_state.htm">
    gpu_get_state()
   </a>
   .
  </span>
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">gpu_set_state(ds_map);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      ds_map
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Data_Structures/DS_Maps/ds_map_create.htm">
        DS Map ID
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The GPU state to set as a
      <span>
       DS Map
      </span>
      .
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">gpu_set_state(gpu_map);
</code></pre>
  The above code sets the GPU state using the map supplied in the variable "gpu_map".
 </body>
</html>